cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.SY, cs.CE 

The paper proposes a new hybrid approach that uses a popular evolutionary search algorithm, CMA-ES, to tune the hyper-parameters of two Long short-term memory(LSTM) ANN models for wind prediction. This approach falls under the category of machine learning and artificial intelligence, which is covered by cs.LG, cs.AI, and cs.NE. The paper also deals with the control and optimization of wind turbines, which is covered by cs.SY. Finally, the paper presents a case study of an offshore wind farm, which falls under the category of computer engineering, covered by cs.CE.
